• Editor's note: This article is updated each time new information becomes available. SYDNEY - World Sevens champions South Africa were whitewashed 29-0 by hosts Australia in the HSBC Sydney Sevens final on Sunday. Australia last won a Sevens title on home soil 16 years ago. READ: Blitzboks reach Sydney final The win also rounded off a great weekend for Australian sevens rugby after they also lifted the women's title on home soil. South Africa's defence was uncharacteristically weak and was at the heart of their defeat after missing several first-time tackles. African News Agency